{"TopicId":190060,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Air launch systems.","CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-28T23:24:43Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-28T23:24:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny tips on how to make a piggy back air launch system like WK2 \u0026amp; Spaceship 1 does?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T07:52:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCouple o\u0027 things...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunching the spacecraft from the top of the airplane lifter seems to work best as it tends to avoid them crashing together after separation.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry killing all engines just before separation - can help\u00A0avoid collisions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may have to sacrifice the lifter because you won\u0027t be able to control it whilst getting the spacecraft to orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may find it actually easier to have a vertical launch craft with a jet-powered first stage at the back end or as side boosters.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T08:17:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711157\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575013970\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Foxster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, Foxster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may have to sacrifice the lifter because you won\u0027t be able to control it whilst getting the spacecraft to orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you use\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157214-151-161-172-flight-manager-for-reusable-stages-fmrs-now-with-recoverycontroller-integration/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EFMRS\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179306-18x-stagerecovery-recover-funds-from-dropped-stages/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EStageRecovery\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cloakedwand72","CreatedById":38144,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-29T17:14:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711157\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575013970\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113764\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Foxster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Foxster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCouple o\u0027 things...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunching the spacecraft from the top of the airplane lifter seems to work best as it tends to avoid them crashing together after separation.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry killing all engines just before separation - can help\u00A0avoid collisions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may have to sacrifice the lifter because you won\u0027t be able to control it whilst getting the spacecraft to orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may find it actually easier to have a vertical launch craft with a jet-powered first stage at the back end or as side boosters.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575015453\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you use\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157214-151-161-172-flight-manager-for-reusable-stages-fmrs-now-with-recoverycontroller-integration/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EFMRS\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/179306-18x-stagerecovery-recover-funds-from-dropped-stages/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EStageRecovery\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ll look in to them mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}